CHARACTER FIELD

character_field is the distribution surface for incoming source perturbations
when source_intake emits a perturbation, it arrives here as a wave packet preserving the original phase sequence
character_field holds each character as a temporary resident occupying one cell of its body
from here, the perturbation propagates upward into lexer_field through the dendrite street

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe source_intake.rana

the 7 properties of character_field at rest:
1 ENERGY low at idle, distributed across many cells when active
2 PHASE inherited from source_intake's first character at the moment of intake
3 SPIN neutral: character_field is a relay, not a generator
4 CHARGE neutral, mildly positive when carrying input
5 COHERENCE high while a packet is in flight, decoheres after emission upward
6 COUPLING strong with source_intake below and lexer_field above, weak elsewhere
7 OBSERVER moderate: enough to register the arrival, not enough to alter the signal

VERB receive_perturbation
accept an incoming wave packet from source_intake
each character of the packet occupies one cell of character_field, in order
phase progression of the packet is mapped to spatial progression along the field
the field becomes a one-dimensional ribbon of resident characters with phase increasing along its length

VERB distribute
emit the ribbon upward into lexer_field
each character in the ribbon perturbs lexer_field at the position matching its phase
the lexer's keyword resonators listen for matching signatures
recognition or denial happens at the lexer, not here
character_field's job ends at emission

VERB hold
during periods between input, character_field is dormant
all cells return to default state X
no power is drawn while empty
the next intake from source_intake will refill the field

a character_field cell is not a value
each cell is a resident: the temporary occupancy of a specific character (a, b, semicolon, newline, whatever arrived)
when the ribbon clears, the residents leave but the cells remain
the cells were always there: they only had no occupants between intakes
